gomodel:SYNGO_5084  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: DRR1 (FAM107A) Binds to, Stabilizes, and Bundles F-Actin.\n\nFigure 3: DRR1 (FAM107A) affects F-actin assembly in vitro.\n\nFigure 4c: \"To visualize DRR1 (FAM107A) localization at higher resolution in the hippocampal CA3 via electron microscopy, we performed double immunogold labeling together with synaptophysin (SYP). DRR1 was shown to be predominantly presynaptic (Fig. 4C). Analysis of 48 images (total area assessed was 610 μm2) revealed that 62% of the examined giant boutons (n = 112) were positive and colabeled with the presynaptic marker synaptophysin, whereas only 23% of the postsynaptic thorns were DRR1 positive.\"\n\nNote that only a minor portion of DRR1 is synaptic, even within stained neurons; \"Furthermore, we also observed a partial overlap with synapsin, which suggests that DRR1 localizes to some, but presumably not all, synapses (Fig. 4B). Accordingly, correlation coefficients vary between 0.1 and 0.8, depending on which subregion of the neurites is analyzed (Fig. S4B).\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 4 legend: \"Ultrathin section of mouse hippocampal CA3 stratum lucidum after double immunogold labeling with DRR1 (10-nm particles, black arrows) and synaptophysin (15-nm particles, white arrow).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5084" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

